# libjxl iteration 3: Malta zero-padding — 2026-04-27

Hardware: AMD Ryzen 9 7950X, 128 GB RAM (WSL2)
Bench commit: 913b966 (post iter2)

## What changed

`lib/jxl/butteraugli/butteraugli.cc` `MaltaDiffMapT()`:

- Allocate `diffs` as (xsize+8) × (ysize+8) instead of (xsize, ysize). Border
  is 4 px on each side. Border stays zero across the lifetime of `diffs`
  (one-time `ZeroMaltaBorder` call); only the interior is rewritten per call.
- Diff precompute writes to `diffs.Row(y+4)[x+4]`.
- Replaced the top/middle/bottom border + interior SIMD path with a single
  flat loop. Every original pixel goes through `MaltaUnit`'s SIMD path; tail
  pixels (x % Lanes != 0) use a 1-lane SIMD MaltaUnit, which is still much
  cheaper than the previous `PaddedMaltaUnit` extract_window path.
- `PaddedMaltaUnit` is now dead code (unused).

`ZeroMaltaBorder` is critical: a naive `ZeroFillImage` of the padded buffer
would zero ~133 MB at 4K and dominate the runtime. The helper zeros only the
4-px border strips (~192 KB at 4K).

## Parity

Bit-identical scores vs unpatched libjxl (same 0.0016% pre-existing Rust↔C++
gap, no new drift).

## Performance (cpp_libjxl, single-threaded)

| size       | iter2     | iter3     | Δ from iter2 | Δ from baseline |
|------------|----------:|----------:|-------------:|----------------:|
| 512²       | 39.5 ms   | 36.3 ms   | -8.1%        | -20.2%          |
| 1280×720   | 215.9 ms  | 215.4 ms  | ~0%          | -15.9%          |
| 1920×1080  | 508 ms    | 513 ms    | +1% (noise)  | -13.1%          |
| 3840×2160  | 2,103 ms  | 2,119 ms  | +0.8%(noise) | -19.4%          |

The win is concentrated at 512² where the border path was a larger fraction
of total work. At 4K, the original SIMD already covered ~99% of pixels
(`x0 + Lanes + 4 <= xsize_` guard), so eliminating the remaining 1% gives
nothing measurable.

The patch is still worth keeping: it's mechanically simpler than the old
top/middle/bottom + PaddedMaltaUnit code, makes Malta a single flat loop,
and gives a clean 8% on 512² where the original border path was painful.

## Cumulative status (cpp baseline → cpp iter1+2+3, single-threaded)

| size       | baseline   | iter1+2+3 | total Δ |
|------------|-----------:|----------:|--------:|
| 512²       | 45.5 ms    | 36.3 ms   | -20.2%  |
| 1280×720   | 256 ms     | 215 ms    | -15.9%  |
| 1920×1080  | 590 ms     | 513 ms    | -13.1%  |
| 3840×2160  | 2,629 ms   | 2,119 ms  | -19.4%  |

## Where the next gains likely live

The Malta diff precompute (lines ~1334-1364 inside `MaltaDiffMapT`) is still
fully scalar with branching on signs. Vectorizing that with copysign-style
branch-free patterns (as in our Rust port) could close more of the gap at
larger sizes — that's the bulk of the remaining 2-3× headroom.
